                {
                    "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13144012/comment/16395564",
                    "id": "16395564",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=llchan",
                        "name": "llchan",
                        "key": "llchan",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Lawrence Chan",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
                    },
                    "body": "Yeah, I was thinking somewhere in the Footer struct, so we don't need to walk all the batches to sum them up.\r\n\r\nAlso they are indeed in the existing RecordBatch metadata, but the current implementation is inside a .cc file and I'd have to either copy+paste or modify my build to expose more of the existing code. Maybe we could expose something like this on the RecordBatchFileReader?\r\n{code:cpp}\r\nStatus ReadRecordBatchMessage(int i, const flatbuf::RecordBatch** metadata) const;\r\n{code}\r\nThen it'd be possible to read the length fields without copying a bunch of code. Not sure if this is a good idea though, since it seems that we dont usually expose the flatbuffers through the public API. Maybe just a \r\n{code:cpp}\r\nint64_t num_rows() const;\r\n{code}\r\nis all I really want, and that can read the new Footer field once it's in there, and walk the batches in the current format?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=llchan",
                        "name": "llchan",
                        "key": "llchan",
                        "avatarUrls": {
